<subSubSection id="EEBF652A015A6672FF12F804FE7F4686" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A61A36A1015A667CFF12F804FA1D41A2" blockId="4.[151,1436,1916,2015]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015A667CFF12F804FEB541C6" bold="true" box="[199,308,1953,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015A667CFE97F807FE2141C6" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[322,416,1953,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015A667CFE97F807FE2141C6" box="[322,416,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">P. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the same area as 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015A667CFC91F807FBD541C6" authority="Bolivar, 1915" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1915" box="[836,1108,1952,1979]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015A667CFC91F807FC3041C6" box="[836,945,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">P. martini</emphasis>
Bolívar, 1915
</taxonomicName>
, but the 
<typeStatus id="791E8803015A667CFB67F804FA9541C6" box="[1202,1300,1953,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
is a nymph; however, 
<bibRefCitation id="C2344B50015A667CFED1F860FE2641A2" author="Walker, F." box="[260,423,1989,2015]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" pagination="425 - 604" refId="ref13004" refString="Walker, F. (1870) Catalogue of the Specimens of Dermaptera Saltatoria in the Collection of the British Museum. British Museum, 3, 425 - 604. [http: // www. archive. org / details / catalogueofspeci 03 britrich]" type="journal article" year="1870">Walker (1870)</bibRefCitation>
wrote “ 
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015A667CFDD7F860FA1D41A2" box="[514,1436,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Keel of the prothorax very high and much rounded, acute in the middle of the fore</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A61A36A1015B667DFF42FF3CFCB9473E" blockId="5.[151,1437,153,324]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFF42FF3CFDC446AA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">border, more acute in the middle of the hind border, near which is slightly dentate. Hind borders of the abdominal segments acutely dentate in the middle</emphasis>
”. These characters match very well those of 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015B667DFBECFF1BFB2746AA" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1915" box="[1081,1190,190,215]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFBECFF1BFB2746AA" box="[1081,1190,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">P. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also Fig. 24 after the plate of 
<bibRefCitation id="C2344B50015B667DFECBFF44FE374681" author="Bolivar, I." box="[286,438,225,252]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" refId="ref11882" refString="Bolivar, I. (1916) Orthoptera. Fam. Acrididae. Subfam. Pamphaginae. Genera Insectorum, 170, 40 pp., 1 pl. [http: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 105422  page / 13 / mode / 1 up]" type="book" year="1916">Bolívar 1916</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015B667DFDC5FF47FDFF4686" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1915" box="[528,638,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFDC5FF47FDFF4686" box="[528,638,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">P. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015B667DFC7AFF47FB8F4686" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[943,1038,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFC7AFF47FB8F4686" box="[943,1038,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">P. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has the priority. Concerning 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015B667DFF42FEA3FE6D4762" authority="Karsch, 1896" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1896" box="[151,492,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subcruciatum">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFF42FEA3FECA4762" box="[151,331,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">P. subcruciatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C2344B50015B667DFE86FEA0FE6D4762" author="Karsch, F. A. F." box="[339,492,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="242 - 359" refId="ref12288" refString="Karsch, F. A. F. (1896) Neue Orthopteren aus dem tropischen Afrika. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 57, 242 - 359." type="journal article" year="1896">Karsch, 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="61A54D22015B667DFD01FEA3FCB24762" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[724,819,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Pagopedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFD01FEA3FCB24762" box="[724,819,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">P. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 21, 23), but their 
<typeStatus id="791E8803015B667DFB92FEA0FBF64762" box="[1095,1143,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
localities are apart (about 
<quantity id="615D9B44015B667DFF42FE8CFF714739" box="[151,240,297,324]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" unit="km" value="600.0">600 km</quantity>
), and it is possible that the former is a valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A61A36A1015B667DFF42F836FD094189" blockId="5.[151,1436,1939,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="94D1EAB3015B667DFF42F836FE9241D1" bold="true" box="[151,275,1939,1964]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">FIGS. 7-12.</emphasis>
